The paper proposes a regularized graph neural network for EEG-based emotion recognition, which involves modeling inter-channel relations in EEG signals via an adjacency matrix. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
